ED visits EDA

# Load data
df <- read_excel("WCTHUG Healthy Viz Competition Dataset.xlsx", na = "(null)")

df <- df %>%
  mutate(arrival_dt = as_datetime(arrival_dt_tm),
         arrival_hour = hour(arrival_dt),
         arrival_dayofweek = wday(arrival_dt, label = TRUE))

Data exploration

Is there anything funny about the data? What’s weird?

Unneeded columns

encntr_type_class_desc_at_admit and encntr_type_desc_at_admit have the same values

df %>% count(encntr_type_class_desc_at_admit, encntr_type_desc_at_admit)

first_triage_acuity_cd codes are not needed as the desc contains them al

df %>% count(first_triage_acuity_cd, first_triage_acuity_desc)

Dependent columns

People who leave without being seen are never admitted

df %>% count(is_admitted, is_left_without_being_seen)

Patterns

Which complaints are true emergencies?

Define true emergency as requiring resuscitation or Emergency

true_emerg_complaints <- df %>%
  group_by(chief_complaint_desc) %>%
  summarise(true_emerg = sum(first_triage_acuity_cd %in% c(1, 2)) / n(),
            n_cases = n()) %>%
  filter(true_emerg > 0.9) %>%
  arrange(desc(n_cases))

print(true_emerg_complaints)

plot_wait_time <- function(group_var) {
  df %>%
    # filter(chief_complaint_desc %in% true_emerg_complaints$chief_complaint_desc) %>%
    # group_by_(group_var) %>% 
    # summarise(
    #   median_wait = median(
    #     arrival_to_first_seen_by_care_provider_elapsed_time_minutes, na.rm = TRUE
    #   ),
    #   n_patients = n()
    # ) %>%
    ggplot(aes(
      x = get(group_var), 
      y = arrival_to_first_triage_start_elapsed_time_minutes,
      group = get(group_var)
    )) + 
    geom_boxplot() +
    xlab(group_var)
}

plot_wait_time("arrival_hour")

plot_wait_time("arrival_dayofweek")

plot_wait_time("start_date_fiscal_period")

Other relationships

Complaint vs wait time

df %>%
  # filter(chief_complaint_desc %in% true_emerg_complaints$chief_complaint_desc) %>%
  group_by(chief_complaint_desc) %>%
  summarise(
    median_wait = median(
      arrival_to_first_triage_start_elapsed_time_minutes, na.rm = TRUE
    ),
    n_patients = n()
  ) %>%
  arrange(desc(median_wait))

Hospital capacity vs wait time by day

df %>%

Duration by time

plot_duration <- function(group_var) {
  df %>%
    filter(start_to_left_ed_elapsed_time_minutes > 0) %>%
    ggplot(aes(
      x = get(group_var), 
      y = start_to_left_ed_elapsed_time_minutes,
      group = get(group_var)
    )) + 
    geom_boxplot() +
    xlab(group_var)
}

plot_duration("arrival_dayofweek")

plot_duration("start_date_fiscal_year_long")

Duration by acquity


plot_duration("arrival_mode_by_ambulance_desc")

plot_duration("first_triage_acuity_desc")

plot_duration("is_admitted")

plot_duration("encntr_type_class_desc_at_admit")

Duration by patient
